Wow! Had me in tears with the beginning affirmation. Today is my 28'th birthday. As someone with anxiety and depression, I have always hated my birthday. I returned gifts, rejected parties and sat at home waiting for friends and family to forget. The wounded child inside could not be happy with anything anyone tried to do for me, and did not deserve to be noticed and loved. But today, I choose to celebrate. I choose to be kind to myself, to recognize growth instead of  my flaws. I choose to love the bundle of purple balloons my husband got for me and to buy myself a gift. I choose to do yoga at home in jammies all day and enjoy my flexibility, instead of feeling like a loser for not currently having a job. I choose to see myself as stronger and wiser then I was a year ago, not the same 'unchanged ' girl with her list of unattained dreams. I choose to see myself as a good mom and a great person. Thanks Adrienne, for helping me feel beautiful and strong from the inside out.

I completely understand the turtle shell/Quasimodo neck reference. My posture was atrocious before I started practicing yoga almost 2 months ago. Tucking my shoulder blades and lifting my heart are what finally connected my awareness to my posture. I've always tried to "stand up straight" but never really under what that meant. Now I think 'slight bend in the knees, tuck your pelvis, draw your shoulder blades together, and lift your heart.' It's becoming second nature. Thank you for that!!

Today was the first day that my local gym finally opened.  We were a small group of 5 mask wearing men and women with VERY low expectations for our performance. Yet, we five came at 6am for what turned out to be an awesome functional fitness class with a tough tabata chaser at the end.  To my surprise, the valslide mountain climbers were not as tough as they were in the past.  My hip flexors weren't screaming!  I have Yoga with Adriene to thank for that.  I may not yet be able to put my heels flat in downward dog and warrior three continues to elude me, but I am getting stronger and BOLDER. ¬†

I've just started yoga camp after finishing the most recent 30 day challenge, Home. A few days ago I managed to achieve one of my biggest goals in life - to make it into wheel pose! I've been doing yoga on and off for many years, and I've also done lots of other workouts, and yet I haven't had the arm strength to do that pose for more than a second or so. I don't think it's just this challenge, but for sure it has helped me massively and it's so addictive to see what daily yoga can do for you.
